  <Notes>
    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>The meanings of πλανάω and πλάνη[a] ({D:31.8}), πλάνος ({D:31.9}), πλάνη[b] ({D:31.10}), and ἀποπλανάω ({D:31.11}) focus primarily upon the misleading or deceptive views which people are caused to have, but these same terms may refer to more than mere mistaken ideas or opinions. They may involve deception of a behavioral nature, and therefore these same meanings could be in Domain 88 Moral and Ethical Qualities and Related Behavior, Subdomain U Mislead, Lead Astray, Deceive.</Content>
    </Note>
    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>It is possible that ἀποπλανάομαι differs slightly from πλανάομαι[b] in emphasizing the departure from truth.</Content>
    </Note>
  </Notes>
